## Overview

A Node.js utility that scans HTML and CSS files to detect image references and copies only the used images to a destination folder. Helps clean up unused assets from projects.

## Features

- ğŸ” Scans HTML files for `<img>` and `<source>` tags
- ğŸ¨ Parses CSS files for `background-image` properties
- ğŸ“‹ Copies only referenced images to target folder
- âœ… Console output for successful operations
- ğŸ—‘ï¸ Helps remove unused images from source folders

## Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Cheerio (HTML parsing)
- fs (file system operations)
- glob (file pattern matching)

## Installation

```bash
npm install
```

## Usage

1. Open `main.js`
2. Configure paths:

```javascript
const sourceDir = '../../portfolio/cat-energy/build/img';      // Source images
const destinationDir = '../Images';                            // Destination (auto-created)
const folderPathHTML = '../../portfolio/cat-energy/build';     // HTML files location
const folderPathCSS = '../../portfolio/cat-energy/build/css';  // CSS files location
```

3. Run:

```bash
node main.js
```

